PO Lifecycle, Calendar Sync, and PO Email — Completion Plan

 Context

 The PO lifecycle redesign (docs/plans/2026-04-09-po-lifecycle-evidence.md) was partially executed today. The goal was to make purchasing surfaces — calendar    
 events, dashboard, daily messages — derive from a single shared lifecycle helper backed by 14 normalized evidence columns on purchase_orders. After auditing    
 the working tree, the visual calendar rewrite landed in source but is uncommitted, the persistence layer is broken in two ways at once, and Tasks 3–7 of the    
 original plan never completed. "Most of the work" exists in pieces but does not add up to perfect functionality.

 This plan brings the calendar, PO email path, and lifecycle persistence to a coherent, working state — committing the salvageable rewrite, fixing the
 schema/code mismatch that is silently failing every PO sync today, then landing the missing writers and dashboard exposure.

 Current State (audit findings)

 What works

 - Migration 20260409000003_fix_po_lifecycle_columns.sql is applied — purchase_orders has all 14 lifecycle columns and 3 indexes; the obsolete lifecycle_state + 
  evidence columns were dropped.
 - src/lib/purchasing/po-receipt-state.ts (untracked) + tests — 4 passing.
 - src/lib/purchasing/calendar-lifecycle.ts (uncommitted rewrite) — new statuses (in_transit / awaiting_tracking / past_due), prefixText, ETA-aware
 getPurchasingEventDate. Tests rewritten in calendar-lifecycle.test.ts — 7 passing.
 - src/lib/purchasing/active-purchases.ts (uncommitted) — uses resolvePurchaseOrderReceiptDate and hasPurchaseOrderReceipt, exposes new isReceived to the        
 dashboard panel.
 - src/components/dashboard/ActivePurchasesPanel.tsx (uncommitted) — consumes isReceived directly from API.
 - src/lib/intelligence/ops-manager.ts calendar sync (uncommitted) — uses getHighConfidenceTrackingForPOs, ETA-driven event dates, new prefixText titles, Oak    
 Harbor LTL parsing, force-update for description encoding cleanup.
 - src/lib/purchasing/derive-po-lifecycle.ts — simplified 5-state helper (sent / vendor_acknowledged / tracking_unavailable / moving_with_tracking /
 ap_follow_up) with 19 passing tests. Used by syncPOConversations.
 - Whole vitest suite: 464 passed / 2 skipped.

 What is broken or missing

 1. CRITICAL — silent write failure on every PO sync. src/lib/intelligence/ops-manager.ts upserts to purchase_orders.lifecycle_state and
 purchase_orders.evidence at lines 915–916, 989–990, 1088, 1152, 1200. Both columns were dropped by migration 20260409000003. Schema column is lifecycle_stage,  
 not lifecycle_state, and there is no evidence column anymore. PostgREST returns errors on undefined columns; these upserts are either erroring on every cycle   
 or silently dropping the lifecycle write while the rest of the row still lands. Either way, the lifecycle write has never reached the DB since the morning fix  
 migration ran.
 2. Task 3 — PO email lifecycle persistence is missing. src/lib/purchasing/po-sender.ts commitAndSendPO() writes only to po_sends (line 326) and ap_activity_log 
  (line 338). It never updates purchase_orders.committed_at / po_sent_at / po_email_message_id / lifecycle_stage. The previous attempt (commit 05bca0c) was      
 reverted in a3dbfa5.
 3. Task 4 — vendor acknowledgement / shipping evidence never landed. Nothing writes vendor_acknowledged_at, vendor_ack_source, shipping_evidence,
 tracking_requested_at, tracking_unavailable_at, tracking_request_count. syncPOConversations only sets vendor_response_at (legacy column) and the broken
 lifecycle_state.
 4. Task 5 — tracking-agent / shipment-intelligence never feed lifecycle columns. Neither src/lib/intelligence/tracking-agent.ts nor
 src/lib/tracking/shipment-intelligence.ts touches purchase_orders.tracking_status_summary, last_tracking_evidence_at, last_movement_summary,
 last_movement_update_at, or shipping_evidence. Tracking truth lives only in the shipments table.
 5. Task 6 — active-purchases API does not expose lifecycle stage. The ActivePurchase interface has no lifecycleStage, lifecycleSummary, lastMovementSummary,    
 trackingUnavailable, or trackingRequestedAt. Dashboard cannot render the new states even after the writers exist.
 6. Calendar sync has two cleanup items in the uncommitted diff.
   - buildPOEventDescription (ops-manager.ts:2204) re-imports getHighConfidenceTrackingForPOs and refetches per PO at line 2216, even though the caller (sync    
 loop, line 2397) already has highConfTracking in scope. Pure N+1; cut it.
   - shouldForceUpdate = true (ops-manager.ts:2453) is a debug flag that defeats the last_tracking change-detection. It should be removed (or scoped to a        
 one-shot env var) before this commits to main.
 7. Repo hygiene. ~20 untracked debugging scratch files at the repo root (check-*.ts, check-*.mjs, force-calendar-*.js, verify-events*.mjs,
 typecheck_output.txt, demo-calendar-update.js, diagnose-*.js, run-sync.mjs, sync-calendar.js, test-po-124557.js, test-regex-3.js) accumulated during the        
 morning's diagnosis.

